# Topicgen — Cybersecurity Topic Generator

A browser-based flashcard-style tool for cybersecurity study and interview preparation. Generates topic cards drawn from a built-in library of MITRE ATT&CK–mapped offensive and defensive techniques, one at a time, with difficulty ratings and save functionality.

No install required. Open the file in any modern browser.

---

## What It Is

Topicgen surfaces cybersecurity topics as study cards for red team and blue team practitioners. Each card presents:

- A **technique name** and **MITRE ID** (ATT&CK for offensive topics, D3FEND for defensive)
- A plain-language **description** of what the technique involves in practice
- A **difficulty rating** (Beginner, Intermediate, or Advanced)
- A **type label** (Offensive or Defensive)

Topics are drawn randomly from the library so repeated sessions surface different content. Cards you want to revisit can be saved to a session list.

---

## How to Run

Open `Topicgen` directly in any modern browser — Chrome, Firefox, or Safari:

```bash
# macOS
open Topicgen

# Windows
start Topicgen

# Linux
xdg-open Topicgen
```

Or double-click the file in your file manager. No server, no npm, no build step required.

---

## Features

| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| **Generate** | Click "Generate Topic" to draw a random card from the library |
| **Type filter** | Switch between All, Offensive, and Defensive topic sets using the tab nav |
| **Save** | Save a card to your session list for later review |
| **History** | Expand the history panel to review all cards generated in the current session |
| **Saved Topics** | View your saved cards in the Saved Topics tab |

> **Note:** Saves and history are in-memory only. Closing or refreshing the browser tab clears all saved data. This is intentional — the tool is designed for focused study sessions, not long-term storage.

