## Intended Use

Topicgen is designed for:

- **Pre-interview warm-up** — run through a set of random cards before a technical interview to activate recall across both red and blue domains
- **Study session structure** — use the type filter to focus a session on offensive or defensive topics
- **Team knowledge checks** — project the tool during team meetings and use generated cards as discussion prompts

---

## Customization

To add topics or modify the library, open `Topicgen` in a text editor and locate the `topicsDatabase` array in the `<script>` section. Each entry follows this structure:

```js
{
  id: 'T1059.001',
  title: 'PowerShell Execution',
  description: 'Use PowerShell to execute commands, scripts, or encoded payloads for initial access, lateral movement, or C2 communication.',
  type: 'Offensive',           // "Offensive" or "Defensive"
  mitreId: 'T1059.001',        // MITRE ATT&CK or D3FEND identifier
  difficulty: 'Intermediate',  // "Beginner", "Intermediate", or "Advanced"
}
```

See [CONTRIBUTING.md](../CONTRIBUTING.md#adding-a-new-topic-to-topicgen) for full guidelines on adding topics consistently.

